A Christmas Game: The Sequel

by Luke A. Jones

You are in Your House.

You can see an Advent Calendar, an Armchair, a Memory Stick, a Shopping List, a Fireplace and a TV.

You can go north or out.

You are in your own home. It is still a modest (i.e. rather too small) town house, which is in a rather chaotic state as you try to prepare for Christmas. The floor is strewn with Amazon delivery boxes. On the wall is an advent calendar with an alarming amount of doors already open.

Just like last year you've left things a bit late and are missing the following essential items for a decent Christmas: Logs for the Fire, A Selection of Cheese, Chestnuts, Some Wrapping Paper,  Sniper Elite 4 Computer Game,a Bottle of Port and a copy of the Bumper Radio Times Christmas Special. You'd better head out into town to get some shopping done, problem is that you've run out of money. Perhaps there are other ways to get what you need.

 (type 'game' for game specific help)

> x list

> x list

It's a list of all the things you need to collect, how useful. You can type 'x list' to quickly check it at any time.

You need:

Logs for the Fire
A Selection of Cheese
Chestnuts
Some Wrapping Paper
A copy of Sniper Elite 4 Computer Game
A Bottle of Port
Bumper Radio Times Christmas Special

> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> x stick

> x stick

A 32Gb memory stick in the shape of a snowman. A present for your friend James who is forever losing them.
> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> x advent

> x advent

It's a traditional advent calendar, with a traditional Minecraft Lego design. There is only one unopened door left (its days are clearly numbered!)
> open it

> open it

You have opened the last door of the advent calendar and can see a chocolate inside
> take chocolate

> take chocolate

You pick it up.
> x it

> x it

A thumb sized chocolate in the vague shape of pixelated axe
> eat it

> eat it

You eat the chocolate. It tastes like advent calendar chocolate, i.e. stale and not very nice
> x armchair

> x armchair

A beautiful oxblood leather wingback armchair that you purchased on Ebay, and had to pick up from some godforsaken industrial estate out of town. You stare at it longingly, but you've too much to do!
> x fireplace

> x fireplace

A real fireplace that you had installed this year. No smoke without fire, and no fire without logs; which is a shame as you've run out of them.
> x TV

> x TV

A 48 inch, full HD, widescreen, smart TV with integrated Blu-ray player. You mainly use it to listen to the radio.
> turn on TV

> turn on TV

You flick on the TV, it is tuned to Radio 3. The sound of Chopin's Nocturne Op 55 No1 comes drifting across the lounge. You'd love to listen, but you have so many things to do. You reluctantly switch it off again.
> x boxes

> x boxes

The amazon boxes fill the room, it doesn't help that they are all so big compared to the contents. The biggest one in the room is nearly the size of the sofa and contained a single memory stick.
> n

> n

You are in Your Garden.

You can see a Shed and a Twisted Thorny Tree.

You can go south.

It's your garden, a modest patch of land where you grow a few things, but there's not much growing this time of year except a few root veg. The ground is soft under foot. At the end of the garden is a rather rickety looking shed.

> x shed

> x shed

A bit rickety and could still do with a lick of paint, maybe next summer.
> open it

> open it

You open it.
It contains a Spade and a Broom.
> x spade

> x spade

It's an excellent spade, in fact you might say it was the ace of spades.

> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> x broom

> x broom

A wooden broom, the handle is screwed into the head. You've changed the head three times and the handle twice, but it's still the same broom.
> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> x tree

> x tree

An ancient looking tree, with a tangle of twisted thorny branches and a tough bark. It was in your garden when you moved in, you've no idea what species it is.
> dig

> dig

You dig a hole.
> x hole

> x hole

A small muddy hole.
It contains a Potato.
> take potato

> take potato

You pick it up.
> x it

> x it

A large round potato, it looks apeeling.
