You are in a Town Square.

You can see a Choir Master.

You can go west, southeast, east, south, northeast or north.

There is a choir here and a brass band, attempting a rendition of "Hark The Herald Angels Sing!", but there is something not right about the relative tempo of the choir and the band. They keep stopping and retrying to get some flow. You can hear tuts and grumbles from the passing shoppers. The Choir Master looks exasperated and forlorn.

> n

> n

You are in Santa's Workshop.

You can see Santa and a 3D Printer.

You can go south.

Apart from Santa sat in his armchair the room is dominated by a huge 3D printer. Scattered and piled up around the room are what looks like poorly printed versions of popular toys; a wonky looking Xbox, a teddy bear that looks like it is suffering from the pox, a bike with sagging oval wheels.

> x Santa

> x Santa

A portly, white-bearded man with half-moon spectacles. He's wearing a red coat with white collar and cuffs, white-cuffed red trousers, and black leather belt and boots. He's sat on a large leather armchair. He looks very sad and his eyes are red as if he has recently been crying.
> x printer

> x printer

A huge industrial scale 3D printer dominates the room
> x Xbox

> x Xbox

A wonky looking 3D printed X-Box. Not only does it look crooked, it obviously has no electronics inside.
> x bear

> x bear

A distorted 3D printed teddy bear that looks like it would give a child (or adult) nightmares for life.
> talk to Santa

> talk to Santa

"Hello my child", says Santa with a sigh, "I'm in a hell of a pickle. After all the grief with the striking elves last year, I decided to replace them with that damn contraption" (he points at the 3D printer). "what a fool I've been, all those children, with no presents to wake up to tomorrow". A single tear flows down Santa’s cheek."

> ask Santa about printer

> ask Santa about printer

"They must have seen me coming." says Santa, "I've never been much good with technology and like a fool I trusted the salesman! How can anyone take advantage of Father Christmas like that."
> ask Santa about elves

> ask Santa about elves

"I sacked the Chief Elf and all the Elves left with him. What a fool I've been, I should put myself on the naughty list."
> ask Santa about xbox

> ask Santa about xbox

"I've never been very good with new technology" says Santa, "I prefer to use magic."
> ask Santa about teddy bear

> ask Santa about teddy bear

"Isn't it just hideous, Ill traumatise the child for life if I put that in their stocking!."
> ask Santa about middle name

> ask Santa about middle name

"Now that's something I've not been asked in a very long time" says Santa, "It's Constantine, after my grandfather."
> turn on printer

> turn on printer

You reach to switch on the printer, but Santa says, "please don't bother, there is no point, everything is makes is garbage."
