> x coin

> x coin

A pound coin, Queen's head on one side, and a Thistle and Royal Diadem on the other. Inscribed around the edge it reads "NEMO ME IMPUNE LACESSIT"
> use coin on jukebox

> use coin on jukebox

You insert the pound coin into the jukebox, a record swings down on to the platter with a satisfying soft clunk. The opening bars of "All I Want For Christmas Is You" by Mariah Carey plays warmly through the room.

At that moment the door to the pub swings open, and in walks a tall lanky chap in an Elf costume. "Jesus, not that tune again!" he says. He orders a gin and tonic and sits down at the bar.
> x elf

> x elf

You can see why this guy is the 'Chief' Elf, he's taller than you! His lanky frame is all arms and legs, he's wearing a green robe trimmed with white fur, a green and yellow striped cone-shaped hat, and yellow stockings.
> talk to elf

> talk to elf

"Hello again." says the Chief Elf, "I've lost my job since I last saw you, damn automation caught up with me."
> ask elf about automation

> ask elf about automation

"Yeah Santa got fed up of our pay and condition demands and replaced us with some kind of wizz bang machinery” says the Chief Elf,  “I hope for the children's sake that it works out for him, but I'm lost without my purpose in life."

> tell elf about printer

> tell elf about printer

You tell the Chief Elf about the disaster in waiting that you have seen in Santa’s workshop, The Chief Elf's eyes widen as you describe the cockeyed presents and Santa's despair.

"Well, well, well" says the Chief Elf, "It will be nice to see old Saint Nick eat humble pie, but first things first, we need to save Christmas, the poor children, I'll round up the gang and head straight over there!"

The Chief Elf bolts out of the door.

