The workshop is a blur of activity. It is packed with a gang of elves who are working at lightening speed producing presents. Every so often the Chief Elf shouts words of encouragement, "Come on lads, we can't let the children down!"

Santa is sat in his armchair checking a very long list.

> talk to Santa

> talk to Santa

"You saved Christmas my child", "There is a lot to do, but the elves are determined that we're not going to let the children down."
> sit on Santa

> sit on Santa

You sit down on Santa's knee. Santa says, "What would like for Christmas?" You whisper in his ear. Santa chuckles and says "Well, you've have been very good this year, and that's a modest request, here you go"

He hands you a big bag of chestnuts."

"The best in the world" says Santa, "friend of mine in Spain always sends me some."
