You are in Glad Tidings Gift Shop.

You can see Gabriel and Wrapping Paper.

You can go east or west.

A gift shop selling cards, wrapping paper, and all manner of elegant gifts and decorations. It is light with a warm glow from candles and white fairy lights.

Alllegri's 'Miserere' plays gently from the shop's sound system, and there is the sweet scent of incense coming from somewhere.

It's normally immaculately organised in here, but it looks like the last minute Christmas shoppers have ransacked the shelves.  All that is left is a couple of rolls of wrapping paper.

> x Gabriel

> x Gabriel

The proprietor of the shop. He is an androgynous and attractive looking fellow. He is barefoot and wearing a huge long blue flowing robe.
> x paper

> x paper

Gorgeous wrapping paper with a depiction of a group of shepherds being visited by an angel. The shepherds look terrified.
> talk to Gabriel

> talk to Gabriel

"Glad tidings!" says Gabriel, "Do not be afraid.. er.. of the mess I mean, it's always like this on Christmas Eve."
> ask Gabriel about paper

> ask Gabriel about paper

"Yeah that design doesn't seem to be too popular, I thought it was pretty funny. Sheperds spook too easy!"
> ask Gabriel about shepherds

> ask Gabriel about shepherds

"Yeah they spook easy those guys."
> listen

> listen

You listen to the shop's sound system, it's playing Allegri's 'Miserere'. You're the secular type, but as the hairs on your neck rise up you have to admit that the devil doesn't quite have all the best tunes.
> x system

> x system

A Bang and Olufsen sound system, seems Gabriel is quite the audiophile. It is currently playing Allegri's 'Miserere'.
> smell

> smell

You sniff and follow the scent of the incense, eventually you discover its source hidden behind one of the displays. There is a platter of gently smoking amber crystals of frankincense.
> x frankincense

> x frankincense

A crystal shapped pale amber coloured lump of Frankincense.
> take it

> take it

You pick it up.
> ask Gabriel about frankincense

> ask Gabriel about frankincense

"Yes I adore the smell of it in the shop".
> ask Gabriel about heaven

> ask Gabriel about heaven

"Heaven?" says Gabriel, "that's a nightclub in the Big City isn't it?"
> ask Gabriel about Christmas

> ask Gabriel about Christmas

"Ahhh!" says Gabriel and he suddenly looks worried, "You've just reminded me, I haven't got round to buying his birthday present, oh well he'll have to settle for socks again, I got some clean ones from some Shepherds."
> tell Gabriel about band

> tell Gabriel about band

Gabriel looks troubled, and something stirs beneath the back of his robe, but a smile breaks out of the corner of his mouth. "Well we can't have that can we? The angels can't hark properly without a trumpet player, and it just so happens that I'm a dab hand."

Gabriel reaches into his desk drawer and pulls out a beautiful golden trumpet, it shines with an angelic light. "OK I'm off to the town square, there is only that wrapping paper left to sell anyway, here have it if you want it" He hands you the wrapping paper and dashes out of the shop. The bell above the door ting-a-lings as he leaves.

