You are in The West.

You can see Gaspar Mouse, Melchior Mouse, Balthasar Mouse and a Tiny Stable.

You can go east.

The Strange Star in the Sky is now directly overhead. As you look it starts to decend to the ground and you realise that it's actually a drone with bright white LEDs on. The drone lands and is picked up by a tiny mouse who is holding the remote control.

"Season's Greeting To You! " says the mouse. "We heard you were a useful and kind human, I thought I could engage your curiosity to lead you here - hence the drone."

"Allow me to introduce myself, I'm Gaspar, these here are my fellow wise mice, Balthasar and Melchior." All three mice bow their heads.

 "We have travelled from the East to worship the new born baby cheesus." "He lies asleep in this stable, for as it was fortold we would find him wrapped in cheesecloth and laid in a manger." "But we cannot enter as we have no appropriate gifts to give." "I don't suppose you have some Gold, Frankincense and Myrrh about your person do you?" says the mouse.

