You are in a The Cheese Hamlet.

You can see a Luxury Cheese Hamper and a Cheesemonger.

You can go north.

A ridiculously posh cheese shop, but my word have they got some produce in here. Every cheese you've heard of any plenty you haven't.  As everywhere else today the shelves are practically bare but in the window is the luxury gigantic hamper of cheese from around the world, exquisite crackers and wonderful chutneys. It brings a tear to your eye, but not as much as the price tag!

> x hamper

> x hamper

The big Daddy of cheese hampers. It contains no less than two dozen different cheese from around the world, plus luxury crackers, chutneys and pickles.
> x cheesemonger

> x cheesemonger

A young man in his twenties, you recognise him as Robin, the son of the owner Mr U'blind, they used to run a butchers shop, but now they run the Cheese Hamlet instead.
> talk to Robin

> talk to Robin

"Hello!" says Robin, "A Merry Christmas to you!".
> ask Robin about hamper

> ask Robin about hamper

"Yes it's pretty much all I've got left. Been a hell of a busy day."
> ask Robin about butchers shop

> ask Robin about butchers shop

"I'm so glad we moved out of the butchery trade" says Robin. "All that mess, the early moring starts at the market, and that damn delivery bike I had to ride about on."
> ask Robin about cheese

> ask Robin about cheese

"We have the finest cheese in all the land in our shop." says Robin, "not cheap of course, but the best is always worth paying for..at least that's what my father reckons."
> give note to Robin

> give note to Robin

You hand the note from Gaspar to Robin. "Ah!" says Robin, 'Well that mouse's credit is good, they spent a fortune in here when they passed through." "Here take the hamper, its the last thing left to sell and I can close early. I've been dying to go and see the choir in the Town Square, they have a brass band playing with them this year."
